  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Perform Split-Stance Pallof Press as a control drill. Create or resist rotational force while breathing, keeping ribs and pelvis organized, and stopping before compensation appears.","setup":["Clear the training area and define the athlete''s start position, finish position, and stop command.","Set band or cable height to match the intended line of pull and keep tension controllable.","Coach one clean practice rep before adding load, speed, partner input, or decision demand."],"execution_steps":["Create the starting position and breathe before tension begins.","Press, hold, row, reach, carry, or resist while preventing unwanted trunk or pelvis rotation.","Reset posture and breathing after each rep or hold; stop when control degrades."],"coach_cues":["Rotate from the ground up.","Ribs and pelvis travel as a team.","Own the finish before the next rep.","Do not let the band or load turn you.","Breathe behind the brace."],"common_faults":["Low back becomes the main rotation point.","Feet lose pressure or the athlete spins on the toes without a controlled base.","Ribs flare, shoulders shrug, or pelvis dumps forward during the turn."],"breathing_cues":["Exhale through effort or release.","Do not hold breath to force rotation.","Recover breathing before the next high-intent rep."],"quality_gate":"The rep counts only if the athlete keeps foot pressure, rib-pelvis organization, clean rotational path, safe finish, and a reset that could be repeated.","stop_signs":["Sharp pain, joint pinch, numbness, tingling, dizziness, or symptom increase.","Lumbar spine becomes the main source of rotation instead of hips, pelvis, thoracic spine, and shoulders.","The athlete loses foot pressure, trunk stack, safe landing, throw accuracy, or controlled reset."]}'::jsonb,
