VALUES (
  'validation_rule',
  'rotational_power_readiness',
  NULL,
  'Rotational power without lumbar twisting under fatigue or wrong phase intent',
  'Rotational athletes need hip-to-trunk-to-shoulder force transfer with spine-sparing rotation — access and sequencing early, anti-rotation in Resilience, loaded strength in Capacity, med-ball throws and cuts in fresh Output.',
  'Top 50 Rotational Athletes and Rotational Power Exercise Library',
  'Build rotational athletes who can access rotation, control rotation, produce force through the ground and trunk, express high-quality rotational power, and brake or redirect rotational momentum safely.',
  'Rotational power is quality-first. Access and sequencing can happen early at low fatigue; high-intent throws, jumps, and cuts belong in Output while fresh; loaded rotational strength belongs in Capacity; anti-rotation and braking belong in Resilience. Stop before speed, accuracy, posture, landing, or trunk control degrades.',
  'Do not chase loaded lumbar twisting under fatigue, turn access work into conditioning, or bury high-intent throws and cuts after the athlete is already tired.'
)
